HEADWORD: Palindrome
<hw>Pal"in*drome</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>pali`ndromos</grk> running back again; <grk>pa`lin</grk> again +
<grk>dramei^n</grk> to run: cf. F. <ets>palindrome</ets>.]</ety> <def>A
word, verse, or sentence, that is the same when read backward or
forward; <as>as, <examp>madam</examp>; <examp>Hannah</examp>; or
<examp>Lewd did I live, & evil I did dwel</examp>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

